MESOSOMA. Pronotum alutaceous, densely pubescent, slightly coarse in most of its surface, presence of some short carinae in its ventral region (
Fig. 4B
). Mesoscutal width 1.2 times its length in dorsal view. Mesoscutum smooth, shiny, almost glabrous except for a few lateral short setae; weak alutaceous sculpture at base of notauli (
Fig. 4A
). Notauli complete with strong transverse carinae; median mesoscutal furrow short but distinct. Parapsidal signum short; parascutal sulcus present, internally carinate, being more distinct in anterior mesoscutum (
Fig. 4B
). Scutellar length 0.6 times that of mesoscutum in dorsal view. Scutellum alutaceous, shiny, completely areolate (
Fig. 4A
). Scutellar foveae rounded, smooth, without any internal carinae, basally defined by a carina; lateral pits of scutellar foveae present but superficial. Interfoveal line present. Circumscutellar carina complete, clearly defined, not dorsally projected at scutellum apex. Mesopleuron glabrous, shiny, with internally carinate transverse groove, presence of more or less extended coarse sculpture in anterior mesopleuron which may not be present in some cases. Mesopleural triangle densely covered by long hyaline hairs. Metanotal troughs densely pubescent. Propodeum heavily alutaceous, pubescent; central area longitudinally divided in two symmetrical areas by median carina; both areas are further divided by short transverse carinae in one big upper cell and two smaller cells.
